    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Relation Extraction Notebook\\n\",\"**NLP Project 29 of 100** — Detect relations like person-works-for-company from text using dependency parsing and patterns.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import spacy, subprocess, sys, re\\ntry: nlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nexcept:\\n    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','spacy','download','en_core_web_sm'])\\n    nlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def extract_relations(text):\\n    doc = nlp(text)\\n    relations = []\\n    # Pattern: PERSON works/worked at/for ORG\\n    for ent in doc.ents:\\n        if ent.label_ == 'PERSON':\\n            for ent2 in doc.ents:\\n                if ent2.label_ == 'ORG' and ent2.start > ent.start:\\n                    span = doc[ent.end:ent2.start].text.lower()\\n                    if any(w in span for w in ['works at','works for','joined','CEO of','founded','leads']):\\n                        relations.append((ent.text, 'works_for', ent2.text))\\n                    elif any(w in span for w in ['left','quit','resigned from']):\\n                        relations.append((ent.text, 'left', ent2.text))\\n    # Pattern: ORG acquired ORG\\n    orgs = [e for e in doc.ents if e.label_ == 'ORG']\\n    for i, org1 in enumerate(orgs):\\n        for org2 in orgs[i+1:]:\\n            span = doc[org1.end:org2.start].text.lower()\\n            if 'acquired' in span or 'bought' in span:\\n                relations.append((org1.text, 'acquired', org2.text))\\n    return relations\\n\\ntexts = [\\n    'Tim Cook works at Apple and previously worked at Compaq.',\\n    'Elon Musk founded Tesla and leads SpaceX.',\\n    'Microsoft acquired GitHub in 2018.',\\n    'Sundar Pichai joined Google as CEO.',\\n]\\n\\nfor text in texts:\\n    rels = extract_relations(text)\\n    print(f'Text: {text}')\\n    for s, r, o in rels:\\n        print(f'  ({s}) --[{r}]--> ({o})')\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Rule-based relation extraction** uses NER + pattern matching on text between entities.\\n\",\"- **Works well for common relations** (works_for, acquired) with explicit language.\\n\",\"- **For complex relations, use transformer-based RE models** (e.g., REBEL, DeepKE).\\n\",\"- **Output format: (subject, relation, object) triples** for knowledge graph construction.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
